member.summary:
The  property indicates if the database should be opened in multi-user or single-user mode.


The  can be used for this property if appropriate.

OptionServerType = connectionString.SingleUser ? "singleUser" : "multiUser";

The  property specifies the full path of your JOOB database directory.


The  can be used for this property if appropriate.

OptionDataSource = "C:\ProgramData\Jade Software\JoobServer1003\system";

member.example:
If you want to delete the methods in the JOOB database that are not in your schema file but you want
to retain existing classes, and properties that are not in the incoming file, specify:

joobLoader.OptionDeleteIfAbsent = false; 
joobLoader.OptionDeleteMethodsIfAbsent = true;

If you want to delete the classes, and methods in the JOOB database that are not in your
schema file but you want to retain existing properties that are not in the incoming file, specify:

joobLoader.OptionDeletePropertiesIfAbsent = false;
joobLoader.OptionDeleteIfAbsent = true;

As shown in the following example.

joobLoader.OptionDataSource = connectionString.DataSource;
joobLoader.OptionConfigFile = connectionString.ConfigFile;
joobLoader.OptionDeleteSchema = "DbAdminTest";
joobLoader.Start();

